# Ganglia


Ganglia is a scalable distributed monitoring system for high-performance computing systems such as clusters and Grids. It is based on a hierarchical design targeted at federations of clusters.

New versions can be downloaded from - http://ganglia.info/?page_id=66

On the back end, Ganglia is made up of the following components:

- **rrdtool**: the Round-Robin Database, is a tool thatâ€™s used to store and display the variation of data over time using graphs.
- **gmond (Ganglia monitoring daemon)**: a small service that collects information about a node. This is installed on every server you want monitored.
Read more about gmond.conf from - http://manpages.ubuntu.com/manpages/yakkety/man5/gmond.conf.5.html
- **gmetad (Ganglia meta daemon)**: a daemon on the master node that collects data from all the Gmond daemons (and other Gmetad daemons, if applicable).
- **PHP web front-end**: a web interface on the master node that displays graphs and metrics from data in the RRD tool.

**Installing Ganglia on CentOS 7**

In our test enviorment I have One Master node and 3 client nodes.

**Master Node Installation & Configuration**

Login to the master node and do the following commands

Ganglia Package Installation
```
yum update && yum install epel-release
yum install ganglia rrdtool ganglia-gmetad ganglia-gmond ganglia-web
```

Set up authentication for the Ganglia web interface (/usr/share/ganglia).

Authentication
```
htpasswd -c /etc/httpd/auth.basic adminganglia
```

Modify /etc/httpd/conf.d/ganglia.conf as follows:

Apache
```
Alias /ganglia /usr/share/ganglia
<Location /ganglia>
 AuthType basic
 AuthName "Ganglia web UI"
 AuthBasicProvider file
 AuthUserFile "/etc/httpd/auth.basic"
 Require user adminganglia
</Location>
```

**Edit - /etc/ganglia/gmetad.conf**

First, use the gridname directive followed by a descriptive name for the grid you are setting up. 

Master Gmetad Configuration
```
gridname "ServerPoint Cluster"Â  #Any Random name
```

Then, use data_source followed by a descriptive name for the cluster (group of servers), a polling interval in seconds and the IP address of the master and monitored nodes.
Note: If a port is not specified then 8649 (the default gmond port) is assumed. 

Master Gmetad Configuration
```
data_source "ServerPoint" 60 64.235.42.76:8649 # Master node
```

Now Edit - /etc/ganglia/gmond.conf

Make sure that these sections have the following and comment any extra lines you see that are within each section.

Master Gmond Configuration
```
cluster {
  name = "ServerPoint"  # The name in the data_source directive in gmetad.conf
  owner = "IT_Team"
  latlong = "unspecified"
  url = "unspecified"
}
 
udp_send_channel {
  #bind_hostname = yes
  # mcast_join = 239.2.11.71
  host = 64.235.42.76  # Ganglia Master Server IP
  port = 8649
  ttl = 1
}
 
udp_recv_channel {
 # mcast_join = 239.2.11.71
  port = 8649
 # bind = 239.2.11.71
  retry_bind = true
  # buffer = 10485760
}
```
Save the changes and exit.

Now the **Firewall Rules, Start the Services & Enabled to Start on Boot**

Firewall Rules and Services
```
firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-service=http
firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-port=8649/udp
firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-port=8649/tcp
firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-port=8651/tcp
firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-port=8652/tcp
firewall-cmd --reload
  
systemctl restart httpd gmetad gmond
systemctl enable httpd gmetad gmond
```

**Client Node Installation & Configuration**

In client node (CentOS) we will only install ganglia-gmond,
If client node is a Ubuntu or Debian then install ganglia-monitor, the equivalent of ganglia-gmond in CentOS.


Ganglia Gmond
```
yum -y install ganglia-gmond
```
Now Edit /etc/ganglia/gmond.conf

This should be identical to the same file in the master node except that the commented out lines in the cluster, udp_send_channel, and udp_recv_channel should be enabled.

Client gmond Configuration

```
cluster {
 
  name = "ServerPoint"
  owner = "IT_Team"
  latlong = "unspecified"
  url = "unspecified"
}
 
udp_send_channel {
  #bind_hostname = yes
  # mcast_join = 239.2.11.71
  host = 64.235.42.76  # Ganglia Master Node IP
  port = 8649
  ttl = 1
}
 
 
udp_recv_channel {
 # mcast_join = 239.2.11.71
  port = 8649
 # bind = 239.2.11.71
  retry_bind = true
  # buffer = 10485760
}
```

Now Restart Gmond service 

Start Gmond
```
systemctl restart gmond
systemctl enable gmond
```
